.094, "y0": 89.971, "x1": 18.623, "y1": 91.397}], "images": [{"x0": 67.75, "y0": 4.89, "x1": 81.9, "y1": 7.06}, {"x0": 7.3, "y0": 4.95, "x1": 39.83, "y1": 7.13}, {"x0": 45.61, "y0": 0.91, "x1": 53.74, "y1": 6.97}, {"x0": 61.24, "y0": 2.03, "x1": 67.91, "y1": 6.75}, {"x0": 10.97, "y0": 10.96, "x1": 67.83, "y1": 13.08}, {"x0": 67.91, "y0": 29.65, "x1": 90.52, "y1": 49.48}, {"x0": 68.11, "y0": 10.17, "x1": 90.32, "y1": 29.74}, {"x0": 10.32, "y0": 28.76, "x1": 39.74, "y1": 43.41}, {"x0": 10.52, "y0": 14.48, "x1": 39.54, "y1": 28.86}, {"x0": 68.07, "y0": 31.78, "x1": 90.52, "y1": 51.29}, {"x0": 9.77, "y0": 36.53, "x1": 39.73, "y1": 50.65}, {"x0": 45.29, "y0": 52.9, "x1": 67.28, "y1": 72.2}, {"x0": 68.52, "y0": 53.43, "x1": 89.97, "y1": 72.21}, {"x0": 51.14, "y0": 74.29, "x1": 87.39, "y1": 91.36}, {"x0": 11.19, "y0": 75.6, "x1": 47.35, "y1": 77.81}], "full_text": "Radiology\nExtradural Hematoma\n(blood is collected bet the dura and brain)\n• Convex towards the brain.\n• Respects the sutures.\n• Usually associated with\nfractures.\n• Doesn’t cross the midline.\n• Significant mass effect(so\nif the patient is not treated\nquickly he will deteriorate)\nSubdural Hematoma\n• Concave or flat towards the\nbrain.\n• Doesn’t respect the sutures\n• Can cross the midline and\ninvolve the dural folds.\n• Less severe mass effect.\n• Can be of different\nchronological age(may wait 1-2\ndays)\nSubarachnoid Hemorrhage\n> Bleeding into the subarachnoid space\n> Linear or small foci within the cerebral\nsulci and CSF cisterns, can involve the\ndural folds.\n> Can be due to rupture aneurysm or AV\nmalformation; Requires further CT\nangiography.\nSubacute Subdural\nHematoma\n1. Asymmetrical brain\n2. It has been there for weeks\n3. No ventricle on one side\n4. Blood ages so it becomes darker\nin colour (Fresh blood appears\nwhite) so we rely on the mass\neffect\n38"}